u zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534141\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534141\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ylh1665702917247.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ylh1665702917247.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ylh1665702917247.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ylh1665702917247\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Delete a record.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__section_hfn_m4q_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d689829e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__p_d130088e1_d130089e1_d130090e1\">For an SQL-like DBMS, the connector must use the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">uiflst</code> structure. This identifies exactly one record by either the\n        primary key or the PRA, and optionally a U_VERSION field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__p_d130091e1_d130092e1_d130093e1\">For an ISAM-like or record-level DBMSs, a Fetch mode 2\n        has prepared locking and positioning. The positioned record is the record to be deleted.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__section_nxh_b2x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d689829e65\">From Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Preconditions realized by Uniface—The table for which the Delete is requested is open.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;TMEnabled</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Indicates whether the connector is\n                TM-controlled.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrv</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was\n                requested in the Info call.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrvini</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Unique identification of the current logon\n                path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;ufldlst</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">The field list which describes all the fields in the\n                table.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uiflst</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Identifies the record to be deleted (SQL-based DBMSs\n                only).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uilist</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Points to the index list.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;sqlbuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15494e1_d15495e1_d15496e1__entry__2\">Points to the SQL buffer.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__section_z25_s2x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d689829e180\">To Uniface</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__2\">Exactly one record was successfully deleted.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-3</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__2\">Exceptional error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-9</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ylh1665702917247__table_d15497e1_d15498e1_d15499e1__entry__2\">DBMS reported network error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__p_d130103e1_d130104e1_d130105e1\">If the connector request return value is less than 0,\n        an error code must be supplied in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>. If more than one\n        record or zero records are deleted, the connector must return an error.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__section_bb2_1cw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d689829e264\">Extra information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">When the row to delete contains segmented fields (that is, there are entries in the field\n        list for which the bitwise AND of <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufbits</code> and the value 8 are non-zero), the\n        connector must also delete the segmented fields.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__section_tlv_tfw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d689829e276\">TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">TM-controlled DBMS connectors are not allowed to begin, commit, or rollback\n        transactions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ylh1665702917247__p_d130115e1_d130116e1_d130117e1\"> For more information, see the \"Transactions\"\n        topic.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cij1665702924062.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transactions</a><p>Transactions play a particular role for stateful components, because these components usually remain active for long periods of time while passing through various states. In principle, each state requires that resources be allocated to it.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534141\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534141\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Delete ('D') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Delete a record. Description For an SQL-like DBMS, the connector must use the uiflst structure. This identifies exactly one record by either the primary key or the PRA, and optionally a U_VERSION field. For an ISAM-like or record-level DBMSs, a Fetch mode 2 has prepared locking and positioning. The positioned record is the record to be deleted. From Uniface Preconditions realized by Uniface—The table for which the Delete is requested is open. Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->TMEnabled Indicates whether the connector is TM-controlled. uctrl->udrv Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was requested in the Info call. uctrl->udrvini Unique identification of the current logon path. uctrl->ufldlst The field list which describes all the fields in the table. uctrl->uiflst Identifies the record to be deleted (SQL-based DBMSs only). uctrl->uilist Points to the index list. uctrl->sqlbuf Points to the SQL buffer. To Uniface Table 2. Connector Request Return Values Value Description 0 Exactly one record was successfully deleted. -3 Exceptional error. -9 I/O server logon error. -16 DBMS reported network error. If the connector request return value is less than 0, an error code must be supplied in uctrl->udrverr . If more than one record or zero records are deleted, the connector must return an error. Extra information When the row to delete contains segmented fields (that is, there are entries in the field list for which the bitwise AND of ufbits and the value 8 are non-zero), the connector must also delete the segmented fields. TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors TM-controlled DBMS connectors are not allowed to begin, commit, or rollback transactions. For more information, see the \"Transactions\" topic. Related Links uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. Transactions Transactions play a particular role for stateful components, because these components usually remain active for long periods of time while passing through various states. In principle, each state requires that resources be allocated to it. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}